               <head>Grant; Needham Street; 1299-1300</head>
               <msContents><textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street</placeName>. 
                        <origDate notBefore="1299" notAfter="1300">1299-1300</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Beuelers</surname>, of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham in the parish of Gaysile)</placeName></persName>, to <persName nymRef="Beuelers">
                           <forename>Beatrice</forename> his daughter</persName>, in consideration of a sum of money, of 6 acres of arable land in Nedham, 3 acres lying in the field called <placeName type="minor">Wethercroft</placeName> next to the land of the said John, and abutting thereon; 2 acres lying in <placeName type="minor">Punchefeld</placeName>, next tot he land of the <persName>lady 'Joyese' of <placeName role="person" key="place_113014">Thelnetham</placeName></persName>, and abutting on the land of the said John; and 1 acre lying in <placeName type="minor">Walkerescroft</placeName>, next tot he land of <persName>
                           <surname>Gilebert</surname> of <surname>Le Hay</surname></persName>, and abutting on the land of <persName>
                           <surname>Hugh</surname> 
                           <surname>(Smith) 'Fabri'</surname></persName>.
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName> on the feast of the Conversion of St Paul, 28 Ed. I [25 Jan. 1299-1300].
                     Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Warenner</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Alexander</forename> 
                           <surname>Bastun</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Mercer</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Cristemasse</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Kersiner</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> 
                           <surname>(Smith) 'Fabro'</surname></persName>.
                     Endorsed: Beweless.
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
